#: ../../M/McQuary-limit.rst:5
msgid "McQuary limit"
msgstr "McQuary limit"

#: ../../M/McQuary-limit.rst:7
msgid ""
"[from the name of the founder of :samp:`alt.fan.warlord`\\; see "
":ref:`warlording`\\.] 4 lines of at most 80 characters each, sometimes still"
" cited on Usenet as the maximum acceptable size of a :ref:`sig-block`\\. "
"Before the great bandwidth explosion of the early 1990s, long sigs actually "
"cost people running Usenet servers significant amounts of money. Nowadays "
"social pressure against long sigs is intended to avoid waste of human "
"attention rather than machine bandwidth. Accordingly, the McQuary limit "
"should be considered a rule of thumb rather than a hard limit; it's best to "
"avoid sigs that are large, repetitive, and distracting. See also "
":ref:`warlording`\\."
msgstr ""
"[\\ :samp:`alt.fan.warlord`\\ の創設者の名前から。\\ :ref:`warlording`\\ "
"を参照]それぞれ最大80文字の4行。\\ :ref:`sig-block`\\ "
"の許容される最大サイズとして、Usenetで今なお時に引用される。1990年代初頭の帯域幅の大爆発以前は、長いsigは実際にUsenetサーバーを運営する人々にかなりの金を費やさせた。今日では長いsigに対する社会的圧力は、機械の帯域幅ではなく人間の注意の浪費を避けることを意図している。したがって、McQuary"
" limitは厳密な制限というより経験則と見なすべきである。大きく、反復的で、気を散らすsigは避けるのが最善である。\\ "
":ref:`warlording`\\ も参照。"
